This paper deals with the problem of solving turn-based probabilistic games with {\omega}-regular objectives, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as the paper deals with formal methods for solving games with logical objectives. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the synthesis of environment assumptions, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
